description:
This branch implements "completion scopes" for KeY.

# Why? 

Completion scopes are a useful extension for designing loop invariant rules (esp. for for-loops) and are used in the definition of the semantics of abstract program elements (-> Abstract Execution), which is why they can be used / are needed for instantiation checking of abstract statements.

# Features and Impact

This branch adds the taclets in file "execRules.key" and extensions to the schema Java / proof Java-parsers. One can write programs like 

```java
    /*@ public normal_behavior
      @ ensures \result == -11;
      @*/
    public int testBreakLabelNonmatchingNested() {
        exec {
            l3: {
                exec { break l3; }
                ccatch (\Return) { return -1; }
                ccatch (\Break) { return -2; }
                ccatch (\Break l1) { return -3; }
                ccatch (\Break l2) { return -4; }
                ccatch (\Continue) { return -5; }
                ccatch (\Continue l1) { return -6; }
                ccatch (\Continue l2) { return -7; }
                ccatch (\Continue *) { return -8; }
                ccatch (Throwable t) { return -9; }
                return -10;
            }
            return -11;
        } ccatch (\Break l3) { return -12; }

        return 42;
    }
```

and taclets like

```
    execReturnVal {
        \find (
            \modality{#allmodal}{.. 
                exec { return #se; #slist }
                ccat ( \Return #t #v ) { #slist1 }
                ccat #cs
            ...}\endmodality(post))
        \replacewith (\modality{#allmodal}{..
            {
                #t #v;
                #v = (#t) #se;
                #slist1
            } 
        ...}\endmodality(post))
        \heuristics(simplify_prog)
       \displayname "execReturn"
    };
```

Adds extensions to the recoder AST classes and corresponding KeY extensions, "exec" statement is registered as new prefix element.

# Review

There are 8 new test cases in automaticJAVADL, run them with `./gradlew :key.core:testRunALlProofs --tests "*completionScopes*"`.

